In endodontic root canal preparation, **lateral compaction** requires a tapered canal form to allow the condenser to move laterally within the canal during obturation, ensuring proper condensation of gutta-percha. This differs from vertical compaction (Option B), which uses a different technique and cavity design. The other options (A and D) are incorrect as they misrepresent the purpose of resistance form in lateral compaction.
